# Vitest Testing

Primary test target: `packages/fuel-core`.

## Required Acceptance Cases

```typescript
// Apollo 11 — mass 28801 → total 51898
// Mars Mission — mass 14606 → total 33388
// Passenger Ship — mass 75432 → total 212161
```

## Edge Cases

- Recursive fuel stops when additional fuel is 0 or negative.
- Single-step flight paths.
- Each planet/action combination (launch/land × earth/moon/mars).

## Conventions

- Co-locate tests with source: `calculate.test.ts` next to `calculate.ts`.
- Use descriptive `it` blocks: `it('calculates Apollo 11 mission fuel', ...)`.
- Test pure functions directly — no WebSocket or DOM in fuel-core tests.
- Full coverage is not required; focus on recursive logic and acceptance scenarios.
